union

public Interval<T> union(Interval<T> other)
The union of this Interval with an another. The result is a Interval from the lowest start to the greatest end Note that union is a commutative operation, meaning that R.union(S).equals(S.union(R)) == true , R and S being instances of Interval.

Parameters:
other -
Returns:
a Interval from the lowest start to the greatest end. Example : [2,3] merged with [7,10] will return [2,10]
